We begin by noting that the Free Cash Flow (FCF) is computed as the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities less the cash outflow for purchasing fixed assets. Also, for the Current Assets Turnover Ratio we use the formula:

  Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average Current Assets

Step 1. FCF Calculation:
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –10,442,735.47
• Purchase of Fixed Assets (CAPEX) = 2,479,994.53
• Thus, FCF = (–10,442,735.47) – (2,479,994.53) = –12,922,730.00

Step 2. Current Assets Turnover Ratio Calculation:
• Initial Current Assets as of 2023-12-31 = 20,000,000.00 
• Ending Current Assets as of 2024-02-05 = 29,413,723.95
• Average Current Assets = (20,000,000.00 + 29,413,723.95) / 2 = 24,706,861.975 
• Main Business Revenue = 28,572,608.70
• Current Assets Turnover Ratio = 28,572,608.70 / 24,706,861.975 ≈ 1.16

Thus, the final result is:

    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "-12922730.00",
    "Current Assets Turnover Ratio": "1.16"
  }
}
